==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rachitis
<hw>Ra*chi"tis</hw> <pr>(r⟦adot⟧*k⟦imac⟧"t⟦icr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>"rachi^tis</grk> (sc.
<grk>nosos</grk>), fr. <grk>"ra`chis</grk>, <grk>-ios</grk>, the
spine.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also <asp>rhachitis</asp>.]</altsp>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Literally, inflammation of the spine,
but commonly applied to the rickets. See <er>Rickets</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A disease which produces abortion
in the fruit or seeds.</def> <rj><au>Henslow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rachitome</ent>⟦br⟧
